'''Anton Alexandrovich Ivanov''' ({{lang-ru|Анто́н Алекса́ндрович Ивано́в}}; born 6 July 1965 in [[Gatchina]], [[Leningrad Oblast]], [[Russian SFSR]], [[Soviet Union]]) is a [[Russians|Russian]] lawyer, businessman, and official. He was a fellow student of [[Dmitry Medvedev]] at the Law Department of [[Saint Petersburg State University|Leningrad State University]], graduating in 1987.

In July 2004 he was appointed First Deputy Director General of the [[Gazprom Media]] holding. He was also a manager of several mass media included in the holding.

On 26 January 2005 he became the Chairman of the [[Supreme Court of Arbitration of the Russian Federation]].

