'''Karl Angelo Maiuri''' is an Estonian [[entrepreneur]] and [[Affiliate marketing|affiliate marketer]]. He is the co-founder of the camera accessories firm [[Tempesta Camera Gear]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Terase|first1=Kristjan|title=Võidukas kaameraliugur kogub austajaid|url=http://www.harjuelu.ee/2014/05/1906/voidukas-kaameraliugur-kogub-austajaid/|accessdate=18 January 2016|work=Harju Elu|date=5 May 2014|ref=awards}}</ref> and the food trading platform SIBIS,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Põlendik|first1=Kadri|title=Noored lõid põllumeeste aitamiseks uue teenuse|url=http://www.aripaev.ee/uudised/2015/12/09/noored-loid-pollumeeste-aitamiseks-uue-teenuse|accessdate=18 January 2016|work=Äripäev|date=9 December 2015}}</ref> which was one of the most active organisations fighting for the rights of farmers in [[Estonia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Estonian students protest in Berlin against the mistreatment of farmers|url=http://maaleht.delfi.ee/news/maamajandus/uudised/eesti-koolinoored-protestisid-berliinis-euroopa-pollumeeste-valjasuretamise-vastu?id=73441439|accessdate=20 January 2016|publisher=Maaleht|date=16 January 2016}}</ref>
==Career== Karl Angelo Maiuri was born 19 September 1998 in [[Salerno]], [[Italy]]. He started school in [[Estonia]] and graduated [[Estonian Business School]] in 2017. He began his career by manufacturing camera accessories for young filmmakers when he was the co-founder of Tempesta Camera Gear.
In 2015 he joined forces with Rudolf-Gustav Hanni to create SIBIS, a food trading platform for local farmers.<ref>{{cite news|title=Farm goods reach consumers through a new app|url=http://maaleht.delfi.ee/news/maaleht/tarbija/talutoit-jouab-posti-teel-tellijateni?id=73147773|accessdate=20 January 2016|agency=Delfi|publisher=Maaleht}}</ref> Since 2015 SIBIS has been fighting actively for the rights of local farmers, to make farming more profitable for farmers and raise the standards of production and product distribution.<ref>{{cite news|title=New app promises to deliver farm goods to door steps in 24 hours|url=http://tarbija24.postimees.ee/3424659/vastne-veebirakendus-lubab-talukaupa-24-tunniga-otse-koju|accessdate=20 January 2016|publisher=Postimees}}</ref>
In 2017 he became the [[Estonia|Estonian]] Country Manager at AdGoals, an innovative [[affiliate marketing]] platform. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://geenius.ee/rubriik/veebimajutuse-blogi/mis-affiliate-marketing-ja-kuidas-see-su-ari-aitab/|title=Veebimajutuse blogi: mis on affiliate marketing ja kuidas see su äri aitab?|work=Geenius|access-date=2017-12-20|language=et-EE}}</ref>
He is the [[Estonia|Estonian]] representative of the international Young Entrepreneurs community.<ref>{{cite web|title=Young Entrepreneurs community - Karl Angelo Maiuri|url=http://yecommunity.com/en/community/karl-angelo-maiuri|accessdate=20 January 2016}}</ref>
==Awards== Karl Angelo Maiuri has been awarded by MAXIMA for his achievements as an "Entrepreneurship talent".<ref>{{cite news|title=Hundreds of youngsters striving to be the "Talent of the Future"|url=http://www.tallinn.ee/est/Uudis-Tulevikutalendiks-purgib-sadu-noori|accessdate=20 January 2016|publisher=Tallinn}}</ref> His company [[Tempesta Camera Gear]] was also claimed the most successful youth start-up of Harju County and the most successful youth ICT and Engineering Start-Up and one of the two nominates for the most successful youth start-up of [[Estonia]] by Entrum.<ref>{{cite news|title=7 Months of Adventures in the Entrepreneurial program ENTRUM|url=http://www.heak.ee/7-kuud-seiklusi-noorte-ettevotlikkusprogrammis-entrum|accessdate=20 January 2016|publisher=HEAK}}</ref>
