[[File:Sharon Gesthuizen 2009.jpg|200px|right|thumb|Sharon Gesthuizen]]
'''Sharon Maria Jacoba Gerarda Gesthuizen''' (born 23 January 1976 in [[Nijmegen]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[politician]] and former [[businesswoman]] and [[trade unionist]]. As a member of the [[Socialist Party (Netherlands)|Socialist Party]] (Socialistische Partij) she was an [[House of Representatives of the Netherlands|MP]] between 30 November 2006 and 23 March 2017.<ref name=parlement>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.parlement.com/id/vhf419quooxk/s_m_j_g_sharon_gesthuizen |title=S.M.J.G. (Sharon) Gesthuizen |language=Dutch |publisher=Parlement.com |date= |accessdate=8 April 2017}}</ref> She focused on matters of [[economy|economic affairs]], [[right of asylum|asylum]] and [[immigration]] policy, and [[judiciary]].
From April till December 2006 she was a member of the [[municipal council]] of [[Haarlem]].<ref name=parlement/>
Gesthuizen grew up in [[Millingen aan de Rijn]] and studied [[art]] at the [[Artez Institute of the Arts]] in [[Arnhem]]. From 2002 to 2003 she was a member of the Dutch [[National Students' Trade Union (Netherlands)|National Students' Trade Union]] (LSVb).
